						               													<description>Ladies and Gentlemen! The most important circuses in the world are looking for Aerial artists, Acrobats, Equilibrists, Illusionists, Jugglers and Clowns. To ensure success, in addition to bringing memorable attractions, each circus also must offer spectators unique delicacies such as cotton candy, candy apples and popcorn. The circus that best satisfies its audience will be chosen as the greatest show on Earth!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;A game of Bravo lasts 17 rounds. In each round, the Master of Ceremonies chooses one of three types of tiles to be acquired by the players: Inner Ring, Outer Ring or Audience. Once the choice is made, a number of tiles equal to the number of players plus one is revealed. A single bid auction is then held to decide who will be the new Master of Ceremonies, who will have the right to be the first to choose one of the open tiles. In a clockwise direction, the other players choose tiles, being able to spend tickets to open new options on the table. When all circuses are completed, players reveal their Ringmaster tile and all artists in each circus are scored. The value of each artist category is added and then multiplied by the number of that category icons in that circus Audience tiles. The player with the most points is the winner.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
